# Literature Review: The Link Between Industry 4.0 and Lean Manufacturing

## Introduction

The operations function plays a crucial role in creating and delivering services and products [1]. Operations management involves making management decisions and designing systems to ensure effective
operations [1]. In recent years, the concept of Industry 4.0 has gained significant attention due to its
potential to transform manufacturing processes. Industry 4.0 refers to the integration of digital technologies and cyber-physical systems in manufacturing [2]. On the other hand, lean manufacturing focuses on
eliminating waste and improving efficiency in production processes [2]. This literature review aims to
explore the relationship between Industry 4.0 and lean manufacturing.

## Industry 4.0 Enables Lean Manufacturing

Research has shown that Industry 4.0 has the capability to implement lean manufacturing practices [2].
Sanders et al. (2016) argue that the research activities in the field of Industry 4.0 serve as enablers for lean
manufacturing [2]. By leveraging digital technologies and data-driven decision-making, Industry 4.0 can
optimize production processes and reduce waste, aligning with the principles of lean manufacturing [2].
Therefore, it can be concluded that Industry 4.0 and lean manufacturing are closely linked, with Industry
4.0 serving as a facilitator for lean practices.

## Limited Studies on the Link between Industry 4.0 and Lean Manufacturing

Despite the potential link between Industry 4.0 and lean manufacturing, there have been few studies
specifically investigating this relationship [3]. Buer et al. (2018) highlight the need for more research in
this area and propose a research agenda to bridge the gap between Industry 4.0 and lean manufacturing
[3]. This indicates that there is still a knowledge gap regarding the specific mechanisms through which
Industry 4.0 and lean manufacturing interact. Future research should focus on exploring the link between
these two concepts to gain a deeper understanding of their interdependencies.

## Concurrent Implementation of Lean Practices and Industry 4.0 Technologies

Tortorella and Fettermann (2018) suggest that the concurrent implementation of lean production practices
and Industry 4.0 technologies leads to larger performance improvements [4]. This finding reinforces
the idea that Industry 4.0 can enhance the effectiveness of lean manufacturing practices. By integrating
digital technologies such as IoT, AI, and data analytics with lean principles, companies can achieve
greater operational efficiency and improved performance outcomes [4]. This highlights the importance
of considering the simultaneous implementation of lean practices and Industry 4.0 technologies for
