maximum benefits.

## Indirect Effects of Industry 4.0 on Sustainable Organizational Performance through Lean Manufacturing Practices

Kamble et al. (2019) emphasize that Industry 4.0 has direct and indirect effects on sustainable organizational performance (SOP) through lean manufacturing practices [5]. Lean manufacturing practices,
which focus on waste reduction and continuous improvement, can contribute to the sustainability of
organizations [5]. By implementing Industry 4.0 technologies, organizations can enhance their lean
practices, leading to improved SOP [5]. This suggests that Industry 4.0 can indirectly influence SOP
through its impact on lean manufacturing practices. Further research is needed to explore the specific
mechanisms through which Industry 4.0 affects SOP.

## Changing Operations Trade-Offs in the Era of Industry 4.0

Olsen and Tomlin (2019) highlight that Industry 4.0 has the potential to change the traditional trade-offs
among cost, flexibility, speed, and quality in goods-producing industries [6]. The integration of digital
technologies in manufacturing processes enables companies to achieve higher levels of customization
and flexibility without sacrificing cost-efficiency and speed [6]. This implies that Industry 4.0 can help
organizations strike a better balance between different operational objectives. Future research should
explore the specific trade-offs and benefits associated with the adoption of Industry 4.0 in different
industries.

## Lean-Digitized Manufacturing as a Viable Business Strategy in the Industry 4.0 Era

Ghobakhloo and Fathi (2019) propose that the development of a lean-digitized manufacturing system can
be a viable business strategy for corporate survivability in the Industry 4.0 era [7]. By combining the
principles of lean manufacturing with digital technologies, organizations can streamline their operations,
reduce waste, and improve productivity [7]. This suggests that lean-digitized manufacturing can help
companies adapt to the changing landscape of Industry 4.0 and remain competitive. Future research should
focus on identifying the specific practices and technologies that enable the successful implementation of
lean-digitized manufacturing.

## Conclusion and Future Research Directions

In conclusion, the literature reviewed indicates a strong link between Industry 4.0 and lean manufacturing.
Industry 4.0 has the potential to enable and enhance lean practices, leading to improved performance
outcomes and sustainable organizational performance. However, there is still a need for more research in
this area. Future studies should focus on exploring the specific mechanisms through which Industry 4.0
and lean manufacturing interact, as well as the trade-offs and benefits associated with their implementation. Additionally, further research is needed to investigate the impact of lean-digitized manufacturing
